cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial landmark detection and facial action unit recognition, which are both tasks related to computer vision. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new framework for simultaneous facial action unit recognition and facial landmark detection using machine learning techniques. Additionally, it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with analyzing facial expressions in videos. Finally, it may belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it has potential applications in human-computer interaction systems.
